    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1877-10-20T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1877-10-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="65" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d65">
                <head>No. 60.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Williamson</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Evarts</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of
                                    the United States at Central America</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Guatemala</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1877-10-20">
                            <hi rend="italic">October</hi> 20, 1877</date>.
                            (Received November 28.)</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 705.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to inform you that President
                        Barrios, of Guatemala, has issued a decree guaranteeing the liberty of the
                        press, with certain restrictions.</p>
                <p>The decree is dated the 15th of October. It has not yet been published in the
                        official journal. A copy and translation of the decree will be sent you by
                        the next mail.</p>
                <p>I would only remark now that the general impression among the better classes
                        here seems to be, that President Barrios has issued the <pb facs="0137" n="75" xml:id="pg_75"/> decree for the purpose of entrapping some of his
                        enemies. There is but little doubt that the unfavorable comments about the
                        killing of the priest, referred to in my No. 701, have had some influence
                        upon the action of President Barrios in this matter.</p>
                <p>I have, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>GEO. WILLIAMSON.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
